39
00:02:17,020 --> 00:02:19,680
front of you or behind you. Because you know what? Your head

40
00:02:19,720 --> 00:02:22,501
and your ears are big sacks of liquid, basically, and they

41
00:02:22,561 --> 00:02:25,922
change the way that your ears receive the sound. And if you do

42
00:02:25,962 --> 00:02:28,522
it right, if you process those sounds right, you'll be able to

43
00:02:28,562 --> 00:02:30,663
distinguish between what's in front of you and what's behind

44
00:02:30,703 --> 00:02:30,783
you.

45
00:02:31,783 --> 00:02:34,384
the next step in spatialized audio is taking into account the

46
00:02:34,444 --> 00:02:36,785
physical properties of the room to get a little bit of echo or a

47
00:02:36,825 --> 00:02:39,585
little bit of dampening. When all these things are done right,

48
00:02:39,665 --> 00:02:43,927
