00:11:37,292 --> 00:11:39,754
going to love that. Controllers, this is a tricky one.

198
00:11:41,055 --> 00:11:45,140
I think we've all had the frustration where we're in

199
00:11:45,200 --> 00:11:47,363
Photoshop and we're trying to crop something to exactly 500

200
00:11:47,804 --> 00:11:51,709
by 500 pixels and getting X and Y at exactly 500 by 500 is just

201
00:11:51,769 --> 00:11:52,870
a big pain in the butt.

202
00:11:55,099 --> 00:11:57,441
When we're in VR, we're working with six degrees of freedom

203
00:11:57,501 --> 00:11:58,402
simultaneously.

204
00:11:58,522 --> 00:12:01,784
And that's just too much to get all those numbers right

205
00:12:02,165 --> 00:12:03,105
at exactly the same time.

206
00:12:03,906 --> 00:12:06,168
So I strongly suggest thinking about ways

207
00:12:06,228 --> 00:12:09,270
of snapping both in position and also in rotation.

208
00:12:09,550 --> 00:12:11,112
In this example, what you do, you

209
00:12:11,252 --> 00:12:14,534
see the ghosted item in your actual position,

